Pivot Using SSH Tunnels and Port Forwarding
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Configure and implement local, remote, and dynamic SSH port forwarding
Create SOCKS proxies for network pivoting scenarios
Use SSH tunnels to access internal network services through compromised hosts
Automate tunnel management using Python scripts
Apply pivoting techniques in penetration testing contexts
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of TCP/IP networking and port concepts
Familiarity with SSH authentication methods
Basic Python programming knowledge
Understanding of penetration testing methodology
