Troubleshooting Tips
Tunnel Connection Fails:

Verify SSH service is running: sudo systemctl status ssh
Check SSH key permissions: chmod 600 ~/.ssh/id_rsa
Ensure target service is accessible: netstat -tlnp | grep [port]
Review SSH logs: sudo tail -f /var/log/auth.log
Port Already in Use:

Find process using port: sudo lsof -i :[port]
Kill existing tunnel: pkill -f "ssh.*-[LRD].*[port]"
Choose different local port for forwarding
SOCKS Proxy Not Working:

Verify proxy is listening: netstat -tlnp | grep 1080
Check proxychains configuration: cat /etc/proxychains4.conf
Test with simple command: proxychains4 curl http://localhost
Ensure PySocks module is installed: pip3 install pysocks
